CREATE EXPRESS APP
create new folder
-npm init
npm install express

create index.js
- const express = require("express")
  const app = express()
  
 
app.get('/', (req, res)=>{})
// this get function is documented at expressjs.com

NODEMON is a package that reloads node when the app changes

to run the app use nodemon appname instead of node appname


+++++++++++++++++++
PORT
to set port to environment variable, in index.js add
const port = process.env.PORT || 3000;
app.listen(port, ()....)
In windows set the Environment variable with
set PORT=4444;
